# Force LF on the git hook and shell scripts. A pre-commit hook checked out with CRLF
# line endings (the Windows default when core.autocrlf=true) can break on its shebang
# line under many shells, and a broken pre-commit hook fails OPEN (it silently stops
# running), which for a security control is the worst failure mode. These rules keep the
# hook executable everywhere regardless of a contributor's autocrlf setting.
hooks/pre-commit    text eol=lf
hooks/install.sh    text eol=lf
*.sh                text eol=lf
